---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base 
  title="Privacy Policy - FaB Collect" 
  description="Privacy Policy for FaB Collect iOS app. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
>
  <!-- Header Section -->
  <section class="py-20 text-center">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-secondary-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300">
        FaB Collect iOS App
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-secondary-500 dark:text-secondary-400 mt-2">
        Effective Date: March 15, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
        
        <p>
          FaB Collect ("we," "our," or "us") values your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our mobile application ("the App").
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect certain types of data to improve app functionality and user experience. The information collected falls into the following categories:
        </p>

        <h3>a. Analytics and Usage Data</h3>
        <p>
          We use analytics services to collect non-personal usage data, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>App interactions (e.g., screens viewed, features used)</li>
          <li>Session duration and engagement time</li>
          <li>Product and card browsing activities</li>
          <li>Device information (e.g., operating system, app version)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>b. Identifiers</h3>
        <p>
          A randomly generated installation ID may be stored on your device to recognize returning users without linking to personally identifiable information.
        </p>
        <p>
          No user accounts or personally identifiable information (such as email addresses) are collected.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>
          We use the collected data solely for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Improving app performance and user experience</li>
          <li>Analyzing feature usage and engagement trends</li>
          <li>Identifying and fixing technical issues</li>
          <li>Ensuring the stability and security of the App</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not use collected data for personalized advertising or user tracking across third-party apps and websites.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We may use third-party services for analytics and app functionality. These services may process data in accordance with their respective privacy policies.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Device Permissions</h2>
        <p>
          The App may request access to the following device features:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Network Access</strong> â€“ To fetch product and card data from external sources, and to download card images.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Product and card data, including card images, is fetched from external sources when needed. No personal collection data is stored or transmitted to external servers, except for anonymous analytics data as described above.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect or store any personal information from children, and we comply with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) by design.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Managing Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          You can delete the app to remove all stored data, including installation ID and any cached product or card information.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the "Effective Date" above. Continued use of the App after an update constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: <a href="mailto:twosixmitch@gmail.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400 dark:hover:text-primary-300">twosixmitch@gmail.com</a>
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-secondary-200 dark:border-secondary-800">  
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

